params.name: data.uri
params.description: The uniform resource identifier of the artifact file. May be empty if there is no actual artifact file.

params.name: data.etag
params.description: An eTag used to perform consistent read-modify-write updates. If not set, a blind "overwrite" update happens.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: The labels with user-defined metadata to organize your Artifacts. Label keys and values can be no longer than 64 characters (Unicode codepoints), can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. No more than 64 user labels can be associated with one Artifact (System labels are excluded).

params.name: data.state
params.description: The state of this Artifact. This is a property of the Artifact, and does not imply or capture any ongoing process. This property is managed by clients (such as Vertex AI Pipelines), and the system does not prescribe or check the validity of state transitions.

params.name: data.schema_title
params.description: The title of the schema describing the metadata. Schema title and version is expected to be registered in earlier Create Schema calls. And both are used together as unique identifiers to identify schemas within the local metadata store.

params.name: data.schema_version
params.description: The version of the schema in schema_name to use. Schema title and version is expected to be registered in earlier Create Schema calls. And both are used together as unique identifiers to identify schemas within the local metadata store.
